### Event QR Generator — HTTP requests
### Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension or JetBrains HTTP client.
### Start the server first:  python app.py   (serves on http://localhost:8000)

@host = http://localhost:8000

### 1. Create an event QR (main request)
# Returns: event_url, qr_svg_url, and qr_data_uri (inline SVG image data URI).
POST {{host}}/api/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rajesh and SriKruthi's Wedding",
  "description": "Join us for a celebration of love and togetherness as Rajesh and SriKruthi tie the knot! We can't wait to share this special day with you.",
  "date": "2026-07-05",
  "time": "06:52 AM",
  "location": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/UdxCjvDdrS3TcL518"
}

### 2. Another example — a minimal event (only required fields: name + date)
POST {{host}}/api/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Team Offsite",
  "date": "2026-08-02"
}

### 3. Open the home page (browser form)
GET {{host}}/

### 4. View the rendered event page directly
### Paste a token from the "event_url" returned by request #1 after d=
GET {{host}}/event?d=PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Fetch the QR image (SVG) for a token
GET {{host}}/qr.svg?d=PASTE_TOKEN_HERE
